1
00:00:05,462 --> 00:00:10,917
Here the body is the biological
expression of the soul’s delusion.

2
00:00:10,917 --> 00:00:14,337
[Delightful Lunatics]

3
00:00:14,582 --> 00:00:20,260
That’s why there is jalajā nava-lakṣāṇi
sthāvarā lakṣa-viṁśati …

4
00:00:20,260 --> 00:00:24,939
Padma-purāṇa is saying:
8 400 000 species.

5
00:00:24,959 --> 00:00:28,622
Don’t trip out on the numbers …

6
00:00:28,622 --> 00:00:33,231
If you take three colors: RGB 
or red, yellow, blue,

7
00:00:33,231 --> 00:00:36,571
whichever three 
you want to deal with,

8
00:00:36,585 --> 00:00:45,015
and start combining them,
you get how many variations?

9
00:00:45,015 --> 00:00:47,022
Millions.

10
00:00:47,022 --> 00:00:51,262
So, taking these three:
tama, raja, sattva—

11
00:00:51,286 --> 00:00:53,256
millions of variations.

12
00:00:53,276 --> 00:00:55,586
That’s what 
they’re telling you.

13
00:00:55,603 --> 00:00:59,537
The body’s the biological expression 
of the soul’s delusion—

14
00:00:59,537 --> 00:01:02,977
it’s the outcome 
of exploiting tendency.

15
00:01:02,977 --> 00:01:03,942
ahaṅkāraḥ,

16
00:01:03,942 --> 00:01:07,812
bhūmir āpo ’nalo vāyuḥ
khaṁ mano buddhir eva ca

17
00:01:07,812 --> 00:01:13,009
ahaṅkāra itīyaṁ me
bhinnā prakṛtir aṣṭadhā
[Bg: 7.4]

18
00:01:13,019 --> 00:01:15,639
Bhagavad-gītā is saying:

19
00:01:15,639 --> 00:01:19,418
these elements,
these mundane elements

20
00:01:19,431 --> 00:01:23,151
form a body,
the gross body

21
00:01:23,170 --> 00:01:27,080
that is built 
upon a subtle body,

22
00:01:27,080 --> 00:01:30,080
which is based upon ego—
ahaṅkāra.

23
00:01:30,080 --> 00:01:36,320
So, it’s all … And what is that,
that ego tendency?

24
00:01:36,330 --> 00:01:38,757
kartāham iti manyate
[Bg: 3.27]

25
00:01:38,767 --> 00:01:42,257
another Gita śloka, 
what does it say?

26
00:01:43,323 --> 00:01:45,236
prakṛti …

27
00:01:48,246 --> 00:01:52,066
kāraṇaṁ guṇa-saṅgo ’sya
sad-asad-yoni-janmasu
[Bg: 13.22]

28
00:01:52,066 --> 00:01:55,906
prakṛteḥ kriyamāṇāni
guṇaiḥ karmāṇi sarvaśaḥ

29
00:01:55,906 --> 00:02:00,506
ahaṅkāra-vimūḍhātmā
kartāham iti manyate
[Bg: 3.27]

30
00:02:00,536 --> 00:02:02,927
It’s saying again:
ahaṅkāra, ego.

31
00:02:02,927 --> 00:02:08,288
The ego of exploitation, 
exploiting tendency

32
00:02:08,288 --> 00:02:16,143
hṛd-rogam—the heart infused 
with consumer tendency

33
00:02:16,143 --> 00:02:19,480
expressing that,
the exploiting tendency—

34
00:02:19,480 --> 00:02:21,764
body is generated from there.

35
00:02:21,764 --> 00:02:25,804
But there’s another world …

36
00:02:27,384 --> 00:02:30,481
paras tasmāt tu bhāvo’nyo 
[Bg: 8.20]

37
00:02:30,481 --> 00:02:31,861
jiva bhuta sanātanaḥ
[Bg: 15.7]

38
00:02:31,861 --> 00:02:35,377
But beyond this world 
there’s another world,

39
00:02:35,377 --> 00:02:40,302
where the body is based upon 
dedicating tendency.

40
00:02:40,302 --> 00:02:45,952
So, Guru Mahārāj said, “In that plane
form and substance are one.”

41
00:02:45,952 --> 00:02:51,102
And I was just remembering,
when I first went to the temple,

42
00:02:51,102 --> 00:02:54,230
the Śrī Śrī Rādhā-Kṛṣṇa Temple

43
00:02:54,230 --> 00:02:58,270
in Haight-Ashbury in 1969, 
December of ’69,

44
00:02:58,270 --> 00:03:02,633
the devotees …
and I say this with affection,

45
00:03:02,633 --> 00:03:07,015
Trivrikam Mahārāj, 
he gets some joy when I say.

46
00:03:07,015 --> 00:03:08,640
He would say,
“What was it like?”

47
00:03:08,640 --> 00:03:12,872
And I said, “I thought 
they were delightful lunatics.”

48
00:03:12,872 --> 00:03:14,047
The group.

49
00:03:14,047 --> 00:03:16,219
But I remember they 
were always telling me this:

50
00:03:16,219 --> 00:03:20,408
they’d point to the sky and say,
“You see that sky?” And I’d go, “Yeah.”

51
00:03:20,408 --> 00:03:25,463
They’d say, “Beyond that sky 
there’s another sky

52
00:03:25,463 --> 00:03:29,483
called the spiritual sky
full of planets.”

53
00:03:29,503 --> 00:03:34,113
And I’m like, 
“Wow man, far out!”

54
00:03:34,133 --> 00:03:37,598
But they’re quoting 
Bhagavad-gītā.

55
00:03:37,598 --> 00:03:42,418
paras tasmāt tu bhāvo ’nyo …
[Bg: 8.20]

56
00:03:42,418 --> 00:03:46,223
beyond this sky, Kṛṣṇa is saying, 
there’s another sky.

57
00:03:46,223 --> 00:03:53,083
So, that world, which is the world 
of our aspiration.

